WEBVTT

00:03.703 --> 00:05.085
Good morning.

00:05.327 --> 00:07.293
You better not be
planning anything special

00:07.335 --> 00:08.698
for our anniversary tomorrow.

00:08.727 --> 00:10.594
Don't worry.

00:10.662 --> 00:12.277
I learned my lesson
last Valentine's Day.

00:12.322 --> 00:13.788
You're not a fan
of grand romantic gestures.

00:13.816 --> 00:14.798
Great.

00:14.867 --> 00:16.900
So, no white doves, Cupid costumes,

00:16.969 --> 00:20.003
or large boom boxes outside of our
window cranking Peter Gabriel?

00:20.072 --> 00:22.305
Not in that... order, no.

00:22.374 --> 00:24.407
Greg, this is our 18th anniversary,

00:24.476 --> 00:25.909
which is traditionally celebrated

00:25.978 --> 00:26.977
by not giving a crap.

00:27.045 --> 00:28.144
How's this for an idea?

00:28.213 --> 00:29.746
I get rid of the kids for a few hours,

00:29.815 --> 00:32.048
and then I make you tacos,
like I did on our first date.

00:32.116 --> 00:33.583
No kids and tacos?

00:33.652 --> 00:35.919
If I had to write a romance
novel, that would be the title.

00:35.988 --> 00:38.822
Mom, tell Anna-Kat
to stay out of my room.

00:38.891 --> 00:41.024
I'm gonna let you in
on a little parenting secret...

00:41.093 --> 00:42.993
I have very little control
over what she does.

00:43.061 --> 00:45.061
Oliver keeps trying on outfits

00:45.130 --> 00:47.898
for his date
with Gina Tuscadero tomorrow.

00:47.966 --> 00:49.799
By the way, this is his mirror face.

00:52.771 --> 00:54.704
So, you finally asked out
Gina from ballet class.

00:54.773 --> 00:56.006
Need any dating tips?

00:56.074 --> 00:57.107
No, I got this.

00:57.175 --> 00:58.508
Okay, but if you change your mind,

00:58.577 --> 01:00.277
there's a boom box with Gabriel
cued up in the basement.

01:01.313 --> 01:02.646
Gina is from South Branson, right?

01:03.682 --> 01:04.915
Finally.

01:04.983 --> 01:07.250
Somebody who can protect my baby
in a street fight.

01:09.087 --> 01:11.988
Trip, I think you misread
the welcome mat.

01:12.057 --> 01:13.557
Morning, Mrs. A.

01:13.625 --> 01:15.125
I'm here to pick Taylor up for school.

01:15.193 --> 01:16.860
Trip, it's "Mrs. O."

01:16.929 --> 01:20.764
"Otto" is spelled "O-T-T-O."

01:20.832 --> 01:22.332
Got it... like "automobile."

01:23.702 --> 01:25.335
- Hey, you!
- Hey, you.

01:25.404 --> 01:26.536
I like your shirt.

01:26.605 --> 01:28.405
Thanks. Shirts are awesome.

01:28.473 --> 01:30.273
I could wear a shirt, like, every day.

01:30.342 --> 01:31.207
Shirts.

01:32.344 --> 01:33.710
Is it possible Taylor's catching

01:33.779 --> 01:35.545
secondary idiocy from this guy?

01:35.614 --> 01:38.014
Let's face it,
she's already no Stephen...

01:38.083 --> 01:39.983
What's his name? The little
genius in the wheelchair?

01:40.052 --> 01:41.618
- Hawking.
- No.

01:41.687 --> 01:44.888
He talks through a computer.

01:44.957 --> 01:45.956
Hawking.

01:46.024 --> 01:47.757
I think it starts with a "V."

01:47.826 --> 01:48.925
I know you want to say "Van Zandt,"

01:48.994 --> 01:51.294
- but I promise you, it's Hawking.
- Whatever, Greg.

01:51.363 --> 01:53.563
I don't like the kid.
Taylor can do so much better.

01:53.632 --> 01:55.131
We got to do something.

01:55.200 --> 01:57.567
Maybe we shouldn't interfere and let
Taylor learn from her mistakes.

01:58.870 --> 02:00.003
Nah.

02:03.842 --> 02:05.008
Hello?

02:05.077 --> 02:06.810
Oh, hi, Principal Ablin.

02:06.878 --> 02:09.446
Ooh! Which one of our three
contestants will be grounded tonight?

02:09.514 --> 02:11.748
I am so sorry to hear that.

02:11.817 --> 02:14.451
Of course. We can come in this morning.

02:19.257 --> 02:20.757
What did you do...

02:24.329 --> 02:25.328
...Anna-Kat?

02:25.397 --> 02:26.496
- Yes!
- Yes!

02:26.565 --> 02:28.498
You're gonna get so grounded.

02:28.567 --> 02:32.302
You can take my life,
but you can never take my...

02:32.371 --> 02:35.205
freedom!

02:35.273 --> 02:36.906
You let her watch "Braveheart"?

02:36.975 --> 02:38.475
Just that snippet.

02:38.543 --> 02:40.577
"Every man dies. Not every man lives."

02:40.646 --> 02:42.312
And the rest of the movie.

02:43.482 --> 02:46.316
